      "description": "The application does not set a Content-Security-Policy (CSP) HTTP response header. Without CSP, browsers have no instruction to block or restrict inline scripts, unauthorized external script sources, or data exfiltration attempts. This significantly increases the blast radius of any XSS vulnerability that may be discovered in the future.",
