      "suggestedFix": "Add a Content-Security-Policy header to all responses. Start with a report-only policy to identify violations before enforcing. For a WordPress blog, a reasonable starting policy is provided below. Tune it based on actual script/style sources used.",
      "codeExample": "# Nginx: Add to server block\nadd_header Content-Security-Policy \"default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://www.google-analytics.com https://www.googletagmanager.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' data: https:; connect-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self';\" always;\n\n# WordPress (wp-config.php or plugin): Use report-only first\n# header(\"Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only: default-src 'self'; report-uri /csp-report-endpoint\");",
